abstract: Safety regulators and Toyota were unable to recreate the sudden unintended acceleration reported by a California owner of a Prius.
snippet: Safety regulators and Toyota were unable to recreate the sudden unintended acceleration reported by a California owner of a Prius.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Toyota said on Monday that the account given by a San Diego man who claimed his Prius hybrid car accelerated out of his control for 30 miles was “inconsistent” with the findings of its initial examination of the car.

headline.main: Toyota Questions Case of Runaway Prius
headline.print_headline: Toyota Says Clues Differ From Prius Driver’s Account
